ist. No red links, please. Do not link multiple occurrences of the same year, just link the first occurrence. If there are multiple people in the same birth year, put them in alphabetical order. Do not trust \"this year in history\" websites for accurate date information. -->\n\n==Deaths==\n*[[911 (year)|911]]  &ndash; [[Pope Sergius III]], pope of the Roman Catholic Church\n*[[1070]] &ndash; [[Gerard, Duke of Lorraine]] (b. c. 1030)\n*[[1099]] &ndash; [[Conrad (Bishop of Utrecht)|Conrad, Bishop of Utrecht]] (b. before [[1040]])\n*[[1132]] &ndash; [[Mstislav I of Kiev]] (b. 1076)\n*[[1279]] &ndash; [[Boles\u0142aw the Pious]], Duke of Greater Poland (b. 1224)\n*[[1322]] &ndash; [[Bartholomew de Badlesmere, 1st Baron Badlesmere]], English soldier and politician, [[Lord Warden of the Cinque Ports]] (b. 1275)\n*[[1345]] &ndash; [[Richard de Bury]], English bishop and politician, [[Lord Chancellor|Lord Chancellor of The United Kingdom]] (b. 1287)\n*[[1424]] &ndash; [[Lucia Visconti]], English countess (b. 1372)\n*[[1433]] &ndash; [[Lidwina]], Dutch saint (b. 1380)\n*[[1471]] &ndash; [[Richard Neville, 16th Earl of Warwick]], English commander and politician (b. 1428)\n*  1471   &ndash; [[John Neville, 1st Marquess of Montagu]] (b. 1431)\n*[[1480]] &ndash; [[Thomas de Spens]], Scottish statesman and prelate (b. c. 1415)\n*[[1488]] &ndash; [[Girolamo Riario]], Lord of Imola and Forli (b. 1443)\n*[[1574]] &ndash; [[Louis of Nassau]] (b. 1538)\n*[[1578]] &ndash; [[James Hepburn, 4th Earl of Bothwell]], English husband of [[Mary, Queen of Scots]] (b. 1534)\n*[[1587]] &ndash; [[Edward Manners, 3rd Earl of Rutland]] (b. 1548)\n*[[1599]] &ndash; [[Henry Wallop]], English politician (b. 1540)\n*[[1609]] &ndash; [[Gasparo da Sal\u00f2]], Italian violin maker (b. 1540)\n*[[1662]] &ndash; [[William Fiennes, 1st Viscount Saye and Sele]], English politician (b. 1582)\n*[[1682]] &ndash; [[Avvakum]], Russian priest and saint (b. 1620)\n*[[1721]] &ndash; [[Michel Chamillart]], French po