rice Druon]], French author (b. 1918)\n*[[2010]] &ndash; [[Israr Ahmed]], Pakistani theologian and scholar (b. 1932)\n*  2010   &ndash; [[Alice Miller (psychologist)|Alice Miller]], Polish-French psychologist and author (b. 1923)\n*  2010   &ndash; [[Peter Steele]], American singer-songwriter and bass player (b. 1962)\n*[[2011]] &ndash; [[Jean Gratton]], Canadian Roman Catholic bishop (b. 1924)\n*[[2012]] &ndash; [[\u00c9mile Bouchard]], Canadian ice hockey player and coach (b. 1919)\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Jonathan Frid]], Canadian actor (b. 1924)\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Piermario Morosini]], Italian footballer (b. 1986)\n*[[2013]] &ndash; [[Efi Arazi]], Israeli businessman, founded the [[Scailex Corporation]] (b. 1937)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Colin Davis]], English conductor and educator (b. 1927)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[R. P. Goenka]], Indian businessman, founded [[RPG Group]] (b. 1930)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[George Jackson (songwriter)|George Jackson]], American singer-songwriter (b. 1945)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Armando Villanueva]], Peruvian politician, 121st [[Prime Minister of Peru]] (b. 1915)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Charlie Wilson (Ohio politician)|Charlie Wilson]], American politician (b. 1943)\n*[[2014]] &ndash; [[Nina Cassian]], Romanian poet and critic (b. 1924)\n*  2014   &ndash; [[Crad Kilodney]], American-Canadian author (b. 1948)\n*  2014   &ndash; [[Wally Olins]], English businessman and academic (b. 1930)\n*  2014   &ndash; [[Mick Staton]], American soldier and politician (b. 1940)\n*[[2015]] &ndash; [[Klaus Bednarz]], German journalist and author (b. 1942)\n*  2015   &ndash; [[Mark Reeds]], Canadian-American ice hockey player and coach (b. 1960)\n*  2015   &ndash; [[Percy Sledge]], American singer (b. 1940)\n*  2015   &ndash; [[Roberto Tucci]], Italian cardinal and theologian (b. 1921)\n*[[2019]] &ndash; [[Bibi Andersson]], Swedish actress (b.1935) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/apr/15/bibi-andersson-obituary|title=Bibi Andersson obituary|