br /><small> (Hong Kong)</small>\n| cable chan 10   = Channel 531\n| cable serv 11   = Surigao Cable TV<br /><small> (Surigao)</small>\n| cable chan 11   = Channel 55\n| iptv serv 1     = [[Singtel TV]]<br /><small> (Singapore)</small>\n| iptv chan 1     = Channel 236 <br />Channel 237 ([[Video on demand|VOD]])\n| iptv serv 2    = [[StarHub TV]] <small> (Singapore)</small>\n| iptv chan 2    = Channel 311<br/>Channel 300 ([[Video on demand|VOD]])\n| iptv serv 3     = [[Now TV (China)|now TV]]<br /><small> (Hong Kong)</small>\n| iptv chan 3     = Channel 442 \n| iptv serv 4     = Mountaintop Cable TV<br /><small>(Philippines)</small>\n| iptv chan 4     = Channel 49 \n| online serv 1   = StarHub TV Anywhere\n| online chan 1   = [https://archive.is/20140208002540/http://www.starhubtvanywhere.com/ Watch live]<br />(Singapore only)\n| online serv 2   = MYTV Super<br /><small>(Hong Kong)</small>\n| online chan 2  = Channel 101\n| online serv 3  = [[TrueVisions#TrueID TV|TrueID TV]]<br /><small>(Thailand)</small>\n| online chan 3  = [https://tv.trueid.net/live/disney-junior Watch live]\n}}\n\n'''Disney Junior''' (formerly known as '''Playhouse Disney''') is a Southeast Asian [[pay television]] channel owned by [[The Walt Disney Company]]. Aimed mainly for children between 2 through 7 years of age, its [[television program|programming]] consists of original first-run [[Children's television series|television series]], theatrically-released and made-for-[[DVD]] [[Film|movies]] and select other third-party programming. Disney Junior also lends its name to an early morning [[block programming|program block]] seen on sister network [[Disney Channel (Southeast Asia)|Disney Channel]], branded as \"'''Disney Junior on Disney Channel.'''\" \n\nThe block was discontinued on July 31, 2018 in favor of using the Disney Channel moniker.\n\n==Feeds==\n* ''Main'': Available in Singapore, Malaysia, Philippines, Indonesia, Thailand, Brunei, Papua New Guinea, Myanmar and Vietnam.\n* ''Hong Kong'': Available in Hong Kong and Macau with its own schedule. Broadcast in [[Cantonese]] and English.\n* ''Taiwan'': Available in Taiwan with its own schedule. Broadcast in [[Taiwanese Mandarin]] and [[English language|English]].\n* ''Mainland China'': Available in Mainland China with its own schedule. Broadcast in [[Chinese language|Chinese]]\n== Programming ==\n\n===Current programming===\nThe channel offers the following programing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://disneyjunior.disney.id/tv-schedule|title=TV Schedule - Disney Junior {{!}} Indonesia|website=Disney Junior {{!}} Indonesia|language=en-ID|access-date=2017-11-10}}</ref>\n====Original programming from Disney Junior USA====\n* ''[[Doc McStuffins]]'' (July 1, 2012\u2013present)\n* ''[[Fancy Nancy (TV series)|Fancy Nancy Clancy]]'' (February 14, 2019\u2013present)\n* ''[[Goldie & Bear]]'' (January 18, 2016\u2013present)\n* ''[[Handy Manny]]'' (July 11, 2011\u2013present) \n* ''[[Henry Hugglemonster]]'' (June 17, 2013\u2013present)\n* ''[[Jake and the Never Land Pirates]]'' (July 11, 2011\u2013present)\n* ''[[Little Einsteins]]'' (July 11, 2011\u2013present)\n* ''[[The Lion Guard]]'' (April 11, 2016\u2013present)\n* ''[[Mickey and the Roadster Racers]]'' (March 24, 2017\u2013present)\n* ''[[Mickey Mouse Clubhouse]]'' (July 11, 2011\u2013present)\n* ''[[Miles from Tomorrowland]]'' (August 17, 2015\u2013present)\n* ''[[Muppet Babies (2018 TV series)|Muppet Babies]]'' (June 25, 2018\u2013present)\n* ''[[My Friends Tigger & Pooh]]'' (2008\u2013201?, October 1, 2016\u2013present)\n* ''[[Puppy Dog Pals]]'' (August 21, 2017\u2013present)\n* ''[[Sheriff Callie's Wild West]]'' (February 24, 2014\u2013present)\n* ''[[Sofia the First]]'' (May 1, 2013\u2013present)\n* ''[[T.O.T.S.]]'' (September 27, 2019\u2013present)\n* ''[[The Rocketeer (2019 TV series)|The Rocketeer]]'' (February 17, 2020\u2013present)\n* ''[[Vampirina]]'' (October 27, 2017\u2013present)\n\n====Original programming from Disney Channel====\n* ''[[Elena of A